data.description:
Experience lakeside living & breathtaking golf course vistas in this classic Willow Springs home. The main floor primary suite plus laundry/sunroom, open & airy floorplan with high ceilings, shiny hardwood floors, & abundance of natural light. 
Front seating & dining area, with its vaulted ceilings, offer incredible views of Kingfisher Lake & the Dakotah hogback through large windows surrounding the wood-burning fireplace. Open eat-in kitchen is fully equipped, w a bar peninsula & dining area. Step out onto the back deck for effortless summer entertainment & barbecues. Living room w unique windows, exposed wood beams, & a stunning moss rock fireplace that extends all the way to the vaulted ceiling. Enjoy sunset happy hours on the deck while welcoming visits from local deer. 
Low-maintenance living with a private feel. Updated powder room & the main floor primary bedroom w ensuite w a spacious glass & tile walk-in shower, a soaker tub, & a dual granite vanity. The cedar-lined walk-in closet is with organizational system. Newly renovated, & super sunny laundry room is just off the main floor bedroom, boasting vaulted wood plank ceilings, skylights, & deck access.
Upstairs, find 2 additional bedrooms, a linen closet, & a renovated full bathroom with granite countertops. The east bedroom offers sunrise lake views, while the west bedroom provides breathtaking sunset foothills & golf course views.
The basement presents a large unfinished space – perfect for a theater room, entertainment area, or play space. Make it your own & instantly increase equity!
Don't miss the chance to call one of the most sought-after west-side communities home! Enjoy foothills living while being minutes away from 470 for easy access to downtown, the Tech Center, or the slopes. Take a short walk or golf cart ride to Red Rocks Country Club, with Kingfisher Lake & a playground across the street. Also included - access to >800 acres of private open space for hiking, biking, or horseback riding!
